<br>
Method 1.  Keep xp the same.<br>
Pre-patch, you have 200k xp (random number), this puts you in lv 59 just barely.<br>
Post-patch, you have 200k xp.  However, since 59 has less xp in it, you're in 58 now.<br>
<br>
Method 2.  Keep level the same.<br>
Pre-patch, you have 220k xp, which is 1 yellow into 59.<br>
Post patch, you still have 1 yellow into 59, but that is now 250k xp.  You just gained a free 30k xp.<br>
<br>
Anyone know? Either way would suck for some people (if you lost a level, or if you didn't get free xp from being in a hell level).<br>
